**Hospital Emergency Room Dashboard (Power BI)**
📌 Project Overview

This project presents an interactive Emergency Room (ER) dashboard built using Power BI, designed to monitor hospital performance, 
patient flow, and operational efficiency.

The dashboard provides both high-level insights (consolidated view) and granular analysis (monthly & patient-level view) to support 
data-driven decision-making in healthcare environments.

🎯 Objectives
Track patient volume and trends
Monitor average wait times
Evaluate patient satisfaction
Analyze admission vs non-admission rates
Identify bottlenecks in ER operations
Support hospital staff in improving response time and care quality
📊 Dashboard Views
1. 📈 Consolidated View

A high-level overview of hospital performance across the selected date range:

Total number of patients
Average wait time
Patient satisfaction score
Number of referred patients
Admission status distribution
% of patients seen within 30 minutes
Department-wise referrals
Patient demographics (race, gender)
Daily patient trends
2. 📅 Monthly View

Focused analysis for a selected month and year:

Daily patient inflow trends
Monthly KPIs (patients, wait time, satisfaction)
Admission breakdown
Department referrals for the selected period
Time-based patient distribution
3. 🧾 Patient Details View

A detailed tabular view providing:

Patient demographics (age, gender, race)
Admission status
Department referral
Wait time per patient
Date-level granularity for deep analysis
🔍 Key Insights
📌 Nearly 50% of patients are admitted, indicating balanced ER intake vs discharge.
⏱️ Average wait time is around 35–37 minutes, highlighting potential optimization areas.
😊 Patient satisfaction remains steady at ~5/10, suggesting room for improvement.
🚑 A significant number of patients are not referred to departments, indicating direct ER handling.
📊 Only about 40–50% of patients are seen within 30 minutes, revealing operational pressure points.
